# Master EC2 Deployment Guide (eBay Project)

This document contains all the correct commands to set up your server from scratch.

---

## 1. Initial System Setup
```bash
# Update System
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install NVM (Node Version Manager)
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
source ~/.bashrc

# Install Node.js 20 (LTS)
nvm install 20

# Install Git & PM2
sudo apt install git -y
npm install -g pm2
```

---

## 2. MongoDB Installation (Local on EC2)
```bash
# Add GPG Key and Repo
sudo apt-get install gnupg curl -y
curl -fsSL https://www.mongodb.org/static/pgp/server-7.0.asc | sudo gpg -o /usr/share/keyrings/mongodb-server-7.0.gpg --dearmor
echo "deb [ arch=amd64,arm64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/mongodb-server-7.0.gpg ] https://repo.mongodb.org/apt/ubuntu jammy/mongodb-org/7.0 multiverse" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mongodb-org-7.0.list

# Install and Start
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y mongodb-org
sudo systemctl start mongod
sudo systemctl enable mongod
```

---

## 3. Project Deployment
```bash
# Clone Repo
git clone https://github.com/dev21sept/KreateList-client-saas.git
cd KreateList-client-saas/backend

# Install Dependencies
npm install

# Setup .env
nano .env
# Paste your keys and MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/ebay_data
```

---

## 4. Run Application (PM2)
```bash
# Create logs directory
mkdir -p logs

# Start using ecosystem file
pm2 start ecosystem.config.js --env production

# Commands to manage app
pm2 status
pm2 logs
pm2 restart elister-backend
```

---

## 5. Nginx Reverse Proxy (Subdomain)
```bash
# Install Nginx
sudo apt install nginx -y

# Configure Proxy
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default
```

**Replace the `location /` block with:**
```nginx
server_name apikreatelist.ajxlubricant.co.in;

location / {
    proxy_pass http://localhost:5000;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
}
```
`sudo systemctl restart nginx`

---

## 6. SSL Certificate (HTTPS)
```bash
# Install Certbot
sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx -y

# Run SSL Setup
sudo certbot --nginx -d apikreatelist.ajxlubricant.co.in
```

